    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Loss of NETO1 leads to impaired GluK1c delivery to distal axons\"\n\nFig.4: \"NETO1 is required for tonic activity of KARs at CA3-CA1 synapse in the neonatal hippocampus\"\n\nFig.5: \"NETO1 deficiency leads to loss of functional presynaptic KARs at immature CA3-CA1 synapses that is rescued with GluK1c overexpression in the area CA3\"\n\n9/7/2018 Pim\n- The data shows that there are less KARs at the presynaptic membrane (ePhys). Since the authors claim that the trafficking of the KARs into the axon is perturbed in Neto1-/- neurons, I have considered the reduced amounts of the NT receptor at the presynaptic membrane (term 'regulation of presynaptic membrane neurotransmitter receptor levels') as secondary and I decided not to make this annotation for Neto1.. Experimental description: - \"Experiments were performed using wild-type (WT), Neto1 -/-, and Neto2 -/- (C57Bl/6NCrl) mice\"",
